# SCSS in `src/admin/` (Customizer / admin bundle)

## Prefer WordPress admin & Customize defaults

- Reuse **core markup and classes** when they fit: `.button`, `.button-primary`, `.customize-control-title`, `.description`, media-style patterns, etc.
- **Do not** override global wp-admin selectors unless scoped under **`#customize-controls`**, **`body.wp-customize`**, or a control root like **`onepress-*-control`** so default WP outside the Customizer is unaffected.
- For colors, borders, and type, stay **visually aligned** with the Customize screen: prefer variables already meaningful in that context; add theme tokens only where core is insufficient.

## CSS variables (high consistency)

- **Shared tokens** (inputs, buttons, borders matching WP): define once (e.g. `:root` at the top of `customizer.scss`) and **reuse** instead of scattering literals — follow the existing `--wp-*`-style names in that file where appropriate.
- **OnePress-only tokens:** `--onepress-…`.
- When changing a “system” value (primary blue, input border), update **one variable** so all controls stay in sync.

## Tailwind-like utility classes (reuse)

- For **layout / alignment / spacing** only (no strong custom look), prefer **existing utilities** at the top of `customizer.scss`: `.flex`, `.flex-column`, `.gap-1`–`.gap-4`, `.justify-*`, `.items-*`, `.w-full`, `.relative`, `.text-center`, etc.
- **New utilities:** same idea — **one job per class**, **kebab-case**, short names (e.g. `.gap-5`, `.min-w-0`). Do **not** redefine WP **component** classes (`.button`, `.media-frame`, …).
- This bundle is usually loaded only in the Customizer, so generic utility names rarely clash; if the same stylesheet is shared with broader admin later, **scope or prefix** utilities if conflicts appear.

## With OnePress controls

- Control shell: `onepress-{feature}-control` (see `scss-css.mdc`).
- Inside: combine **functional** inner classes with utilities, e.g. root `onepress-typo-control` plus `flex gap-2 items-center` on a row that needs no bespoke styling.

## After edits

- Run **`npm run build`** from the theme root.
